{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:56.225064+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here is a summary of the findings from the repository.\n\n---\n\n## 📦 npm Scripts (from `package.json`)\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `start` | `react-scripts start` | Run the development server |\n| `build` | `react-scripts build` | Create a production build |\n| `test` | `react-scripts test` | Run the test suite |\n| `eject` | `react-scripts eject` | Eject from Create React App configuration |\n| `predeploy` | `npm run build` | Automatically run **build** before deployment (hook for `deploy`) |\n| `deploy` | `gh-pages -d build` | Publish the `build` folder to GitHub Pages |\n| `clean-files` | `rm -rf ./template/public ./template/src` | Remove template copies (used before republishing the npm template) |\n| `copy-files` | `cp -a ./src/. template/src && cp -a ./public/. template/public` | Copy source files into the `template/` directory (used before npm publish) |\n| `prepublishOnly` | `npm run clean-files && npm run copy-files` | Prepares the template directory just before `npm publish` |\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 Guidance for Testing a Production Build Locally\n\nThe **README** provides the following optional procedure to verify the production build works correctly before deploying to GitHub Pages:\n\n1. **Temporarily change the `homepage` field** in `package.json` to `\"/\"` (this ensures asset paths are relative, so the build works when served from a subdirectory or locally).\n\n2. **Install the `serve` package globally** (if you don’t already have it):\n   ```bash\n   npm i -g serve\n   ```\n\n3. **Build and serve the production bundle locally**:\n   ```bash\n   npm run build-and-serve\n   ```\n   > **Note:** The `build-and-serve` script is **not actually defined** in `package.json`. The README mentions it, but you would need to either create that script yourself (e.g. `\"build-and-serve\": \"npm run build && serve -s build\"`) or run the two steps manually:\n   > ```bash\n   > npm run build\n   > serve -s build\n   > ```\n\n4. After verifying the local production build, **remember to restore the `homepage` field** in `package.json` back to your actual GitHub Pages domain (e.g. `http://your-github-username.github.io/your-repo-name`) before running `npm run deploy`.\n\n---\n\n### Key Takeaway\n\nThe repository is a **Create React App template** (npm package `cra-template-firebase-starter`) aimed at quickly scaffolding a React app with Firebase authentication, Material UI, routing, and one‑command GitHub Pages deployment. The local production test step is an optional quality check: build the app, serve it with `serve`, verify everything works, then reset `homepage` and deploy.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1100, "prompt_tokens": 7795, "total_tokens": 8895, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 448, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4736}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 4736, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 3059}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "a8615c0c-5ddf-4cde-887b-7e5702c003c8", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e7-0052-70f2-9f4b-ff4911ac5438-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 7795, "output_tokens": 1100, "total_tokens": 8895, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 4736}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 448}}}}]}}}
